This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Spoken Language Understanding. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, self-attention mechanisms, and meta-architectures, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to the task, which involves sampling schemes, indicating a possible connection to the sub-category of cs.LG (Learning). The use of siamese and triplet energy-based meta-architectures suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions experiments and evaluations, which are commonly associated with the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
